DAMATURU – Around 12:30 Midnight of Saturday after a heavy rainfall in Damaturu which resulted to overflooding in communities behind white House, Ali Marami, Yobe State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) recieved distress call of Building collapse and Victims including children and infants trapped in the collapse building said Dr. Mohammed Goje, Executive Secretary SEMA. “With the support of Volunteers, SEMA evacuated 17 victims from 4 Households ( 6 adults, 7 children and 4 infants) to Specialist Hospital Damaturu. The victims are currently on admission and receiving treatment free at Yobe State Specialist Hospital”. ES SEMA thanked the medical team at the State Specialist Hospital Damaturu Accident and Emergency unit for there tremendous effort in responding to the victims.